-align: -0.338ex; width:6.301ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle m=
=3D0}"></span></b>.</li>
<li>A "vertical" line has undefined or infinite slope (see below).</li></ul=
>
<p>If two points of a road have altitudes <i>y</i><sub>1</sub> and <i>y</i>=
<sub>2</sub>, the rise is the difference (<i>y</i><sub>2</sub> =E2=88=92 <i=
>y</i><sub>1</sub>) =3D =CE=94<i>y</i>. Neglecting the <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Figure_of_the_Earth" title=3D"Figure of the Earth">Ear=
th's curvature</a>, if the two points have horizontal distance <i>x</i><sub=
>1</sub> and <i>x</i><sub>2</sub> from a fixed point, the run is (<i>x</i><=
sub>2</sub> =E2=88=92 <i>x</i><sub>1</sub>) =3D =CE=94<i>x</i>. The slope b=
etween the two points is the <b>difference ratio</b>:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e m=3D{\frac {\Delta y}{\Delta x}}=3D{\frac {y_{2}-y_{1}}{x_{2}-x_{1}}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=CE=94<!-- =CE=94 --></mi>
              <mi>y</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=CE=94<!-- =CE=94 --></mi>
              <mi>x</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <msub>
                <mi>y</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <msub>
                <mi>y</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <msub>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <msub>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle m=3D{\frac {\=
