=3D"600"></a><figcaption>Slope of a line in coordinates system, from <span =
class=3D"nowrap"><i>f</i>(<i>x</i>) =3D =E2=88=9212<i>x</i> + 2</span> to <=
span class=3D"nowrap"><i>f</i>(<i>x</i>) =3D 12<i>x</i> + 2</span></figcapt=
ion></figure>
<p>The slope of a line in the plane containing the <i>x</i> and <i>y</i> ax=
es is generally represented by the letter <i>m</i>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-5" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slope#cite_note=
-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</s=
pan></a></sup> and is defined as the change in the <i>y</i> coordinate divi=
ded by the corresponding change in the <i>x</i> coordinate, between two dis=
tinct points on the line. This is described by the following equation:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e m=3D{\frac {\Delta y}{\Delta x}}=3D{\frac {{\text{vertical}}\,{\text{chan=
ge}}}{{\text{horizontal}}\,{\text{change}}}}=3D{\frac {\text{rise}}{\text{r=
un}}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=CE=94<!-- =CE=94 --></mi>
              <mi>y</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=CE=94<!-- =CE=94 --></mi>
              <mi>x</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mtext>vertical</mtext>
              </mrow>
              <mspace width=3D"thinmathspace"></mspace>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mtext>change</mtext>
              </mrow>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mtext>horizontal</mtext>
              </mrow>
              <mspace width=3D"thinmathspace"></mspace>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
