</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/172550f94371f0e63473266a49766c04df02e309" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:7.227ex; height:2.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle y_{=
2}-y_{1}}"></span> (<i>rise</i>). Substituting both quantities into the abo=
ve equation generates the formula:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e m=3D{\frac {y_{2}-y_{1}}{x_{2}-x_{1}}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <msub>
                <mi>y</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <msub>
                <mi>y</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <msub>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <msub>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle m=3D{\frac {y=
_{2}-y_{1}}{x_{2}-x_{1}}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/72263d5113a7cc985f29fc9fc4b3f5e85dd5bbe5" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.171ex; width:14.23ex; height:5.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle m=
=3D{\frac {y_{2}-y_{1}}{x_{2}-x_{1}}}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>The formula fails for a vertical line, parallel to the <span class=3D"mw=
e-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inli=
ne mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www=
.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle y}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>y</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle y}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/b8a6208ec717213d4317e666f1ae872e00620a0d" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:1.155ex; height:2.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle y}"=
></span> axis (see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Division_by_zer=
o" title=3D"Division by zero">Division by zero</a>), where the slope can be=
 taken as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infinity" title=3D"Infin=
ity">infinite</a>, so the slope of a vertical line is considered undefined.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Examples">Examples</h3><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DSlope&amp;action=3De=
dit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: Examples"><span>edit</span></a>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Suppose a line runs through two points: <i>P</i>&nbsp;=3D&nbsp;(1,&nbsp;=
2) and <i>Q</i>&nbsp;=3D&nbsp;(13,&nbsp;8). By dividing the difference in <=
span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xml=
ns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle y}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>y</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle y}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/b8a6208ec717213d4317e666f1ae872e00620a0d" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:1.155ex; height:2.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle y}"=
></span>-coordinates by the difference in <span class=3D"mwe-math-element m=
we-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-math=
ml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Mat=
h/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle x}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>x</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle x}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/87f9e315fd7e2ba406057a97300593c4802b53e4" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.33ex; height:1.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle x}">=
</span>-coordinates, one can obtain the slope of the line:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e m=3D{\frac {\Delta y}{\Delta x}}=3D{\frac {y_{2}-y_{1}}{x_{2}-x_{1}}}=3D{=
\frac {(8-2)}{(13-1)}}=3D{\frac {6}{12}}=3D{\frac {1}{2}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=CE=94<!-- =CE=94 --></mi>
              <mi>y</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=CE=94<!-- =CE=94 --></mi>
              <mi>x</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <msub>
                <mi>y</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <msub>
                <mi>y</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <msub>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <msub>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mn>8</mn>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mn>13</mn>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>1</mn>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>6</mn>
            <mn>12</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle m=3D{\frac {\=
Delta y}{\Delta x}}=3D{\frac {y_{2}-y_{1}}{x_{2}-x_{1}}}=3D{\frac {(8-2)}{(=
13-1)}}=3D{\frac {6}{12}}=3D{\frac {1}{2}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/d5afc54d2730fbe906f1926981074f3e06f4c285" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.671ex; width:44.858ex; height:6.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle m=
=3D{\frac {\Delta y}{\Delta x}}=3D{\frac {y_{2}-y_{1}}{x_{2}-x_{1}}}=3D{\fr=
ac {(8-2)}{(13-1)}}=3D{\frac {6}{12}}=3D{\frac {1}{2}}.}"></span></dd>
<dd>Since the slope is positive, the direction of the line is increasing. S=
ince |<i>m</i>| &lt; 1, the incline is not very steep (incline &lt;=E2=80=
=8945=C2=B0).</dd></dl>
<p>As another example, consider a line which runs through the points (4,&nb=
sp;15) and (3,&nbsp;21). Then, the slope of the line is=20
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e m=3D{\frac {21-15}{3-4}}=3D{\frac {6}{-1}}=3D-6.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mn>21</mn>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>15</mn>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mn>3</mn>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>4</mn>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>6</mn>
            <mrow>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>1</mn>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mn>6.</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle m=3D{\frac {2=
1-15}{3-4}}=3D{\frac {6}{-1}}=3D-6.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/69cef55373bce032897a822809760033130b958f" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.005ex; width:27.086ex; height:5.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle m=
=3D{\frac {21-15}{3-4}}=3D{\frac {6}{-1}}=3D-6.}"></span></dd>
<dd>Since the slope is negative, the direction of the line is decreasing. S=
ince |<i>m</i>| &gt; 1, this decline is fairly steep (decline &gt;=E2=80=89=
45=C2=B0).</dd></dl>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Algebra_and_geometry">Algeb=
ra and geometry</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editse=
ction-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?titl=
e=3DSlope&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section: Algebra=
 and geometry"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">=
]</span></span></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Slopes_of_Parallel_and_Perpendicular_Lines.sv=
g" class=3D"mw-file-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/w=
ikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7a/Slopes_of_Parallel_and_Perpendicular_Lines.svg/=
250px-Slopes_of_Parallel_and_Perpendicular_Lines.svg.png" decoding=3D"async=
" width=3D"250" height=3D"333" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D=
