</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>For example, consider a line running through points (2,8) and (3,20). Th=
is line has a slope, <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m</i></span>, of=20
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\frac {(20-8)}{(3-2)}}=3D12.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mn>20</mn>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>8</mn>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mn>3</mn>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>12.</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\frac {(20-8=
)}{(3-2)}}=3D12.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/2feb369cb521542408ae5879c3ae96b9c94a0f6f" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.671ex; width:15.043ex; height:6.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
frac {(20-8)}{(3-2)}}=3D12.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>One can then write the line's equation, in point-slope form:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
