<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Other_uses">Other uses</h2>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</sp=
an><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DSlope&amp;action=
=3Dedit&amp;section=3D11" title=3D"Edit section: Other uses"><span>edit</sp=
an></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The concept of a slope or gradient is also used as a basis for developin=
g other applications in mathematics:
</p>
<ul><li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gradient_descent" title=3D=
"Gradient descent">Gradient descent</a>, a first-order iterative optimizati=
on algorithm for finding the minimum of a function</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gradient_theorem" title=3D"Gra=
dient theorem">Gradient theorem</a>, theorem that a line integral through a=
 gradient field can be evaluated by evaluating the original scalar field at=
 the endpoints of the curve</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gradient_method" title=3D"Grad=
ient method">Gradient method</a>, an algorithm to solve problems with searc=
h directions defined by the gradient of the function at the current point</=
li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conjugate_gradient_method" tit=
le=3D"Conjugate gradient method">Conjugate gradient method</a>, an algorith=
m for the numerical solution of particular systems of linear equations</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonlinear_conjugate_gradient_m=
ethod" title=3D"Nonlinear conjugate gradient method">Nonlinear conjugate gr=
adient method</a>, generalizes the conjugate gradient method to nonlinear o=
ptimization</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stochastic_gradient_descent" t=
itle=3D"Stochastic gradient descent">Stochastic gradient descent</a>, itera=
tive method for optimizing a differentiable objective function</li></ul>
